race.comment: WHATALEGACY (2) has led all the way and not been headed in his two starts to date, the latest and most impressive performance coming at Kembla over 1000m where he cleared right away. Ratings indicate he is at home in this company so worth following. SOCIAL CIRCLE (5) tasted defeat for the first time when she just failed to get to Petticoat in a 1000m Randwick Highway 16 days ago. Definitely looking for the extra trip now so she will be very tough to hold out. MISS FREELOVE (3) tried hard but found the winner a shade too good when resuming over this distance at Canterbury recently. Returned a career-best figure when second-up over today's journey last prep. Serious contender. PERLE DE CHOCOLAT (4) ran on stoutly to grab third in the same race as MISS FREELOVE at Canterbury last start. Cherry ripe now and is one to watch for late in proceedings. MATIMA (1) resumes for new trainer Gary Portelli. Competitive in Saturday company last prep so must be a threat.
